---
description: Do not hardcode Unity GUIDs or asset IDs in code
alwaysApply: true
---

# No Hardcoded GUIDs

Never hardcode Unity asset identifiers in C# or other source code:

- Asset GUIDs (`052faaac586de48259a63d0c4782560b`)
- Input action / action map IDs
- Magic strings for `FindAction`, `FindActionMap`, `Resources.Load`, `AssetDatabase.LoadAssetAtPath`

## Use instead

- `[SerializeField]` references: `InputActionReference`, prefabs, materials, ScriptableObject assets
- ScriptableObject settings assets assigned in the Inspector
- `[CreateAssetMenu]` for project configuration (input, balance, enemy params)

## Examples

```csharp
// BAD
inputActions.FindAction("351f2ccd-1f9f-44bf-9bec-d62ac5c5f408");

// GOOD
[SerializeField] InputActionReference moveAction;
moveAction.action.ReadValue<Vector2>();
```

```csharp
// BAD
[SerializeField] string actionId = "641cd816-40e6-41b4-8c3d-04687c349290";

// GOOD
[SerializeField] PlayerInputSettings settings;
settings.MoveAction.ReadValue<Vector2>();
```

## Manual YAML / prefab edits

Do not hand-author `InputActionReference` `.asset` files or GUID-based links in prefabs. Configure references in the Unity Editor.

If a reference is missing after codegen, tell the user which Inspector field to assign — do not patch GUIDs into code.

## Private field naming

All private fields in C# must use a leading underscore:

- Instance fields: `_mover`, `_isEnabled`
- `[SerializeField]` private fields: `_settings`, `_walkSpeed`
- `const` / `static readonly` private fields: same rule if they are fields (not local variables)

Public members, properties, and method parameters keep normal PascalCase / camelCase — no underscore.

When renaming an existing serialized private field, add `[FormerlySerializedAs("oldName")]` so Unity keeps Inspector assignments.

```csharp
// BAD
[SerializeField] PlayerInputSettings settings;
PlayerMover mover;

// GOOD
[SerializeField] PlayerInputSettings _settings;
PlayerMover _mover;
```

## Explicit access modifiers

Always write the access modifier on methods — do not rely on the default `private`:

- Unity lifecycle: `private void Awake()`, `private void Update()`
- Helpers: `private void SetCursorLocked(bool locked)`
- Public API: `public void SetControlEnabled(bool enabled)`

```csharp
// BAD
void Update()
{
}

// GOOD
private void Update()
{
}
```
